# AI Agent Rules for Tiation Projects

## MANDATORY READING
All AI agents working on Tiation projects MUST read:
- TIATION_AGENT_DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md (complete deployment system)
- deployment-configuration-report.md (status report)

## DEPLOYMENT SYSTEM STATUS
- 12 repositories fully configured with enterprise-grade Surge deployment
- Automated CI/CD workflows implemented
- Security headers and performance optimization active
- Dark neon theme consistency enforced across all projects

## ESSENTIAL COMMANDS
- `npm run deploy:surge` - Deploy to production
- `npm run health-check` - Verify deployment
- `./scripts/deploy-all-repos.sh` - Configure all repositories
- `node scripts/generate-deployment-config.cjs <repo-name>` - Configure new repos

## THEME REQUIREMENTS
- Dark neon theme with cyan/magenta gradients
- Enterprise-grade UI components
- Consistent branding across platforms
- Professional documentation standards

## SECURITY REQUIREMENTS
- HTTPS/TLS enforcement with HSTS
- Content Security Policy headers
- XSS and clickjacking protection
- Security scanning in CI pipeline

## PERFORMANCE STANDARDS
- HTTP/2 support enabled
- Gzip and Brotli compression
- Optimized caching strategies
- Lighthouse CI performance monitoring

## AUTOMATION STATUS
✅ Repository configuration automated
✅ Mass deployment system implemented
✅ CI/CD workflows deployed
✅ Security scanning integrated
✅ Performance monitoring active
✅ Dark theme consistency enforced

## AGENT RESPONSIBILITIES
1. Always verify deployment configuration exists
2. Test deployments after making changes
3. Maintain dark neon theme consistency
4. Follow security best practices
5. Use automated scripts for repetitive tasks

